<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-31T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-31T04:00:00-05:00" n="808" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/827: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-31T18:00:00+09:00">December 31, 1938—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 31—7:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>818. Department’s 435, December 30, 7 p.m.<note n="24" xml:id="d808fn24">Not printed.</note> The organic regulations of the China Board were
                            promulgated on December 16 on which date the Board was organized and
                            began to function. Our despatch 3549, December 23<note n="25" xml:id="d808fn25"><ref target="frus1938v03#pg_431">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 431</ref>.</note> on this
                            subject was sent forward in the pouch leaving on the day following.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>